{
  "texts": [
    "The core of this approach lies in the adoption of a hybrid fusion strategy that incorporates both early and late fusion methodologies.",
    "Early fusion is applied at the input level where raw data from different modalities are initially combined using a feature alignment network, which maps disparate data into a unified feature space.",
    "Subsequent layers then employ a late fusion approach where higher-level semantic features are integrated just before the final decision-making layers.",
    "This allows the model to maintain modality-specific processing while also leveraging cross-modal interactions at different stages of the information processing pipeline.",
    "This algorithm outlines the specific steps within the hybrid fusion process, utilizing early and late fusion to maximize the coherence and relevance of the integrated multimodal features."
  ]
}